glosses: To accuse, to make an allegation.

examples.text: Agrippina, bir çok antik tarihçi tarafından İmparator Claudius'u zehirlemekle itham edilmiştir.
examples.translation: Agrippina was accused by many ancient historians of poisoning Emperor Claudius.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish اتهام ایتمك (ithâm etmek). Compound of itham (“accusation, allegation”) + etmek (“to do, to make”).
